caption: The pan fried pork dumplings were good! but the pork belly ramen was LACKLUSTER. When you think of a pork based ramen you think of a rich fatty pork flavored soup base and nice flavored pork pieces, this has none of that. The egg was also way over done for a ramen bowl. If you want ramen order from somewhere else, but if you want dumplings this is the place to go!
Amazing soup dumplings
Incredible. The pork fried dumplings were so good and survived a lengthy delivery (not the restaurant's fault). Great flavors and menu variety but the dumplings are always going to be the best item

Such a nice local place I strongly recommend! It is located little bit far from main city. You should take metro Line No.1 or other and get off at Columbia station, it is a walking distance. If you take no.1 metro, it is Manhattan music school, it is also walking distance. Within 10mins you can get there.  Every dumpling I had was all good really. Eveu I ordered 2 more such as Pork chicken. Local people like music school students guranteed this place. Go now! Gogogo
It was very tasty. I had two different types of dumplings and a noodle. They were all yummy. Staffs were very nice too.

Excellent dumplings.  Great noodle dishes.  Try the crabmeat dumplings, you won't be disappointed.

Nice Chinese place for delicious dumplings, along Broadway. I have tried almost all dumplings on their menu & my favorite is the Chicken Dumplings with Spicy Vinaigrette. Shrimp is great too. Taro milkshake is luscious & inviting. Moderately priced & Best for group dining.
Delicious food. Trendy place. Rice bowl was delicious.
Not as good at it use to be.
I've been coming here for years. A bit pricy, but the soup dumplings are very good. The low mein is probably the best value and is a whole meal. Enjoy!
Great value for money. Tasty food. Not cheap Styro plates of sugary food.
Amazing affordable dumplings. I love their pot of green tea
Visit this place and order one of everything.
Good food and staff.
Far and away the best Chinese food place in Morningside. If you go, be sure to get some soup dumplings!
Delicious food for a reasonable price! The staff is very friendly and accommodating, and the food came out quickly. Nice atmosphere too.
Pretty yummy food! I got pork dumplings and the scallion pancakes. Both were not shabby but a little on the pricey side.

Incredible food!! Highlights were Beef Scallion Pancake, Pork Xiao Long Bao, and Dong Jing Rice Bowl. Really nice, calming vibe inside of the restaurant as well. Service is fast too! As a newbie to Asian cuisine, this was an amazing overall food experience! Definitely will be back for some great soup dumplings and rice bowls 🤙🏻
First time I have been to this place and it was really good. Glad that I gave them a try. These are kimichi dumplings. Soo good.
Nice atmosphere. The food is very good.
Absolutely delicious Dan Dan Noodles and soup dumplings.   Great authentic cuisine.
Tasty dumplings. Nice atmosphere. A bit expensive.

The beef and soup in beef noodle soup are great! Beef is perfectly braised. However, I don't understand why they use really thin noodles. Real authentic beef noodle soup comes with thick noodles not these thin ones... The lo mein is pretty good and the dumplings are ok.

There are two branches for this restaurant here in Manhattan. One is up on 125th St. and the other is closer to Lincoln Center. They’re both fantastic. The food is delicious. I love the sesame noodles and also the pan fried pork dumplings. This is the kind of place that I’m sure would be fantastic regardless of what you order. I can tell it would all be delicious. They are just great.  Also, the service has always been fantastic, too. Really nice people.
Luv this place
Very good dumpling! And the rest of the dishes looks good also! Go try it!
Amazing soup dumplings and chicken fried rice.
Great Chinese food...enjoy there noodles
Aurhentic Shanghai soup dumplings. The real deal. Avoid the Americanized dishes.
Food are decent and fast.
Only had steamed pork dumplings. Service was good dumplings were delicious.

Great spot to stop by for a quick bite. Yummy, flavorful dumplings in a nice atmosphere on the Upper West Side.

Great service and tasty food, I really recommend the chicken dumplings in spicy vinaigrette. It was fantastic! Also the pork kimchi xiao long bao is subtly spicy and very delicious.

I'm proud Harlem has a dumpling house called the dumpling room that can hold it's own weight. You can get burly pork dumplings uptown without the trip to Chinatown or Flushing. The proportions were really good, very filling / flavorful. The fried shell's texture doesnt overpower the filling which is awesome, but the steam dumpling was purfecto . It's not messy, its fresh out the kitchen and it immediately hits the spot. I could go on & on about my Sunday, but the point is, what's the point of going to the dumpling spot if you're not gonna order dumplings?? Will be back for all the dumplings next time!
La Salle Dumpling is "Awesome!!!" The service is "Fantastic!!!" The food is "Fresh and Delicious!!!"

Decent sized place can usually get a seat without a problem. The dumplings are good but not a huge range considering they’re named dumpling room. The other offerings are good but it’s not my favorite Chinese place in the area. That said we still go fairly regularly, it’s not bad.
Worth every penny.  A giant step up from  usual "take-out" Chinese fare.

Compared to other Chinese restaurants in the neighbourhood, the Dumpling Room is certainly a good choice. But unfortunately from my past experiences of ordering and eating there, I am not particularly impressed by either the taste of the food or the quality of ingredients. The dumplings do not taste very fresh and the quality of fried rice is lacking. I would only recommend going there when you really crave Chinese food and do not want to travel the distance to eat at an authentic Chinese restaurant that serves fresh high quality Chinese good.
I ordered that pork belly ramen and got sick
Enjoyed everything we had. Soup dumplings were extra great.
Great service and dumplings. My soup however, was very very oily. 5 stars to the crab and pork soupy dumplings!

Good authentic Chinese food with relaxing atmosphere. One of the best in the area. The offer wide range of Chinese food with a twist. However, sometimes the staffs’ English is not great and they put in wrong orders.
Good bite

NG! The dining room smelled like a catbox, maybe they keep cats to police rodents or something but srsly, smelled like a cat box. The fried dumplings were horrible, looked like mini tacos, were not like gyo-za at all.

The dumpling room has been a special treat for my family for the past six months. The staff is always very kind and the food is amazing!  Don’t miss this little spot hidden under the one train. Great for families where kids can watch the train run by every few minutes. Thanks La Salle Dumpling Room!
Really good food, deserving of the accolades. I've had dumplings as advertised. They were pretty good. 4/5
Lovely dumplings great service.

Ordered pork dumplings with crabmeat and coconut milk bubble tea. Dumplings were so good had to order another round but with shrimp. 5/5 Bubble tea was great, too, not too sweet. It was very quiet for Sunday afternoon, waitresses was very attentive, overall good experience, would like to come back to try pan fried dumplings and specials.

Stopped here while working. Called in an order for pick, very fast service. Order the Product belly Ramen and the Pork Belly sandwiches. Both were very tender and delicious. I would ask for a little more of the sauce on the sandwich but that is a minor complaint about great food.

Not authentic Xiaolongbao and dumpling. I do not recommend if you are Chinese. The skin was so thick. Can't believe they had pork and kimchi flavor since kimchi is Korean. Tastes strange. And it's my first time to see a waiter collect tips in front of your face. We are not leaving yet! Like they tried to hurry you out.
Love their dumplings! They are usually busy so plan accordingly.

I love coming here. Everything is so delicious and the prices are great as well. After I discovered this place it has become one of my favorite places for a quick bite.

You have to get a side of the spicy vinegar sauce that only comes on the chicken dumplings. It goes good with everything and everything was great.
Really good dumplings

Really wanted to like this place as it’s the only soup dumpling this part of town. I’m sad to say we were so unhappy with our food we left halfway to get pasta next door. Xiaolongbaos (soup dumplings) here had unbelievably thick and dry skin, the soup inside tasted like MSG, not sure they even qualified as soup dumplings. And the scallion pancake tasted like nan bread from the supermarket.  I’m surprised this place lasted for so long but guess there’s no other options around. The decorations and service were good though and I can’t say the food was horrible...it’s just not chinese food.
The vibe is great. I got a bunch of stuff, but the beef scallion wrap and the Xiao buns were my favorite items. I recommend.

Difficult to find soup dumplings this good outside of Chinatown and flushing. Authentic Shanghainese take on their dumplings and food. Get the little pepper spicy beef noodle soup and the beef scallion pancakes.

Great Chinese food. If you are looking for a better quality Chinese food, then you should come over here! You can pick up and dine in. The food is a little pricey. However, you could taste the quality of food in compare to your traditional Chinese food.

Great staff and great food! It's a bit tiny to eat there in person so I like to do delivery and these guys rock! Go for the Dong Jing rice bowl as it's really tasty and the delivery staff are speedy and nice. Love these folks :)

Fantastic dumpling house. We'd ordered delivery from here before and it was very tasty, but it's a comfy place to eat at... high ceilings and retro-decor. The food obviously here is the star.  Dumplings had to be on point and they were. Scallion pancake roll ups were delightful. General Tso was fine. Nothing special, but that's not what you come here for. 5 Dollar beers were a pleasant surprise. Lastly, they were super accommodating to our 3 year old and 20 month old. HOME RUN!!!
Good but a bit pricey for what you get.

Best soup dumplings I've had since Din Tai Fung in Hong Kong! Cumin beef is fantastic. Selection of slushes and smoothies are worth trying (and inexpensive). Cute decor, clean. Overall prices are a little high but worth it, I think.

Went here pre dinner rush hour on a weekend and quite liked it!  We really liked the soup dumplings. They were flavorful and the dough was a medium thickness which I like. Scallion pancake, however, was a bit meh, considering the $8.50 price. We also had the hot diced chicken, which was also a bit disappointing. Not hot at all (the slightest hint of spice) and definitely too salty. Service was prompt and courteous.

Atmosphere is cozy with the lighting and decor. I did not feel the dumplings justified the price. Would likely revisit for a noodle or veggie dish instead.

The flavors were mostly there, but the dumplings were kinda doughy, especially the soup dumplings. The top quarter of them have an unpleasant texture. Disappointing considering the place is called the friggin dumpling room! Also that beef scallion pancake thing looks waaaayyyy better than it tastes. Seems like there are a few main ingredients that get repurposed for several different dishes but they are all so similar that it just wasn’t exciting. But, I might stop back in and give it one more try since it’s by my house. I would not go out of the way to eat here that’s for sure. Sorry dumpling room! I wanted to love you so much :/

I think the dumpling here is good. The hand made dumpling with the fresh pork and scallion is a homesick food for me. A great place to visit and hang out with friends. Dumplings are very good but not if you want the traditional ones. The decor is beautiful and modern. They adapted the food for a more younger crowd with a trendy twist.

honestly the dumplings were not that impressive.. Go Cafe China instead..

This is the most authentic Chinese and Taiwanese-style food outside of Flushing. Just plain delicious. Of course it costs a bit more than cheap takeout- it is cuisine, not fast food! Still incredibly cheap for the phenomenal food you get. There is no tougher critic than my wife, who is from Taiwan and loves it too; our only issue is that we eat too much every time we go!
Upscale Chinese place. High ceiling, pictures of old New York, creative design. And place is perfectly clean. Dumplings could be better but General Tso Chicken is almost perfect.

Lasalle Dumplings is a brand new restaurant with amazingly scrumptious dumplings ! I visited recently on a Sunday evening and was greeted by Sam the manager and the very pleasant wait staff. The pork & vegetable dumplings, fried rice and general T'so chicken was all freshly prepared and served hot. Highly recommended for couples, groups or families. The restaurant is pleasantly decorated and you can view into the kitchen where the meals are prepared. I had the opportunity to meet the lady that preps the dumplings. She speaks very little English and has the most delicate small hands, just right for fine art of tasty dumpling making ! Go there now !!
